reviewText: The course is slow.

So much of the content was limited without paying for the course, that calling it a MOOC is a real stretch.  Because of these limitations, most of my work was done on my own, and by purchasing the related book.  Since my local Community College used to run this course, but now points to this onine course instead, it's a huge disappointment.  Most folks who are going into business for themselves need good information but have little cash.  The one star is for the handouts (I believe pulled from other websites but pointed to by this course) - these have been useful.
It was really boring, just reading the text in the presentation.It can be made in 4 classes not 8.
Informative but not challenging enough.

I have given you a 2* star rating as on finishing my course promptly all the information I submitted has suddenly been locked! I haven't been able to answer a classmate's request to review his work & worse, I haven't been able to print off my own work for reference & this is a REAL project so I need to be able to do this. We were not given notice that this would happen.#disappointed
​I did learn some, im more of a hands on person

I​t is an easy to follow course that gives a good overview over the Business Model Canvas. However, I found it sometimes not easy how to come up with the specific points to write into the Canvas from the questions we were exploring. More details and explanations would have been valueable.
very good, i suggest to add more examples and extra explanation, especially for value proposition since it is the main block

It was nice, considering the messages and the amount of time. However, participation and feedback by others was really limited.
descriptions was not enough for me, the BMC concepts could be more elaborated by giving examples and explaining different types of businesses.
Still waiting for my assignment grades for weeks 1-3 despite having had many people mark these.
If you are new in the learning of business model generation is a choice to start with. But if you already have some experiencie this course is very very basic.
Great Course. Excellent Narration.

Plus: Practical. You produce the business model for your business. Minus: Except the practical steps (”plus”, above) it somewhat like getting the Business Model Canvas book read to you. Polish the content, more real world examples and war stories (like the very good Nestlé story).

The instructor is very monotone and struggles with the scripted material. I ended up using the text portion and just reading it because I found it distracting.

Some of the peer review are not formal, just click on to pass next topic, and this is not objective.
